title: I Ching - Of the Marsh and the Moon (Flac) [FrankFoo]
description:
I Ching - Of the Marsh and the Moon (flac)

Credit David Chesky with putting out--at least occasionally--some really intriguing music. 

This work consists of several tracks played by three Chinese musicians with traditional 
instruments, and an American synthesist. 

The choice of material is flawless--a perfect mix of ancient songs and new compositions. 

The playing is great, creating moods of beauty and serenity. 

While there are quite a few CDs available in the worldbeat category, 
none that I know of does what this album does, which is to envelope the 
listener in a deep feeling of Chinese life. 

You may not be in China, but you definitely understand what it may be like, at least sensually.

Linage: CD > EAC > flac

Included: NFO, PLS, M3U, LOG, CUE
